      • removeLocation

        public boolean removeLocation(Location location)
        Removes the given Location instance from the list of Location instances.

        If this SequenceAnnotation object belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDcouement instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        Parameters:
        location -
        Returns:
        true if the matching Location instance is removed successfully, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - if the associated SBOLDocument is not compliant.

      • setComponent

        public void setComponent(String displayId)
        Sets the reference Component URI to the URI of the Component instance matching the given displayId.

        If this SequenceAnnotation object belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDcouement instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        This method creates a compliant URI for the reference Component instance using the persistent identity of this SequenceAnnotation object's parent ComponentDefinition instance, the given displayId, and the parent ComponentDefinition instance's version. It then calls setComponent(URI) to set the reference.

        Parameters:
        displayId -
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - if the associated SBOLDocument is not compliant
        IllegalArgumentException - if the associated ComponentDefinition object is not null, and the given componentURI does not exist in its associated ComponentDefinition object's list of Component instances.

      • setComponent

        Parameters:

        Throws:
